The paper deals with kernelization, a technique commonly used in parameterized complexity, which is closely related to the study of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The problems studied in the paper are combinatorial optimization problems, which are often studied in the context of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper also mentions the concept of fixed-parameter tractability, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT).
